From Git Bash

$cd Desktop
$git clone (paste here the URL of the Repository created online with github) https://github.com/.../.../Test.git
$cd Test
$ls
README.md
$vim README.md (you can also edit with Notepad by clicking on Test on the Desktop).
[after inserting the message type ESC several times and then type ":" followed by "q" for quit without saving, or "x" for saving]
$git add README.md
$git commit -m (or -F for file) "updated README file"
$git log
$git status
$git push -u origin master
##type when prompted "RInterested" and password
$touch testfile.txt (creates a new file in the local directory)
